OL,5,EHOMELESSNESS IS CRIMINAL? Qjj  
OL,7,BAbout a quarter of young people going  
OL,8,Binto custody areEhomelessBwhen they    
OL,9,Bcommit the crime, says NACRO officer   
OL,10,BPaul Cavadino.                         
OL,12,B"Also, half of young offenders who had 
OL,13,Bhomes when imprisoned find they do not 
OL,14,Bhave homesEwhen they get out,"Bhe adds.
OL,16,E"It's a vicious circleB- people coming 
OL,17,Bout of prison are more likely to offend
OL,18,Bif they don't have a home, and they end
OL,19,Bup back in prison again."              
